Democracy Index and Global Contributors¶

Gabi Capone

This notebook focuses on global contributors to changes in democracy indices between 2012 and 2022.

It appears that Latin America, Central, South, and Southeast Asia, Central Africa, and Eastern Europe have experienced a decrease in democracy scores since 2012.

In [1]:
import geopandas

import pandas 

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn

import numpy

plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = [9, 6]

linewidth = 0.05

csv = pandas.read_csv("https://github.com/gcapone2/cybergisx/raw/main/democracy-index-eiu.csv")

countries = geopandas.read_file("https://michaelminn.net/tutorials/data/2019-world-energy-indicators.geojson")

merged_data = countries.merge(csv, left_on="Country_Code", right_on="Code", how="left")

import esda.moran

import splot.esda

import pysal.lib

import pysal.model

residuals["ID"] = range(residuals.shape[0])

res_weights = pysal.lib.weights.Queen.from_dataframe(residuals, ids="ID")

res_weights.plot(gdf=residuals, indexed_on="ID")

plt.show()


residuals["Residuals"] = residuals["Residuals"].fillna(0)

moran = esda.moran.Moran(residuals["Residuals"], res_weights)
splot.esda.plot_moran(moran, zstandard=True, figsize=(10,4))

plt.show()
